        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 6:58PM EDT by NWS Cleveland OH</headline>
        <description>At 658 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Findlay, moving southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Findlay, Bluffton, Arlington, Rawson, Benton Ridge, Jenera, Mount
Cory, and Williamstown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
